DataElement.preferredDefinition: A unit of knowledge created by a unique combination of characteristics. (ISO 1087)_In the Unified Medical Language System (UMLS) of the National Library of Medicine (NLM) the concept unique identifier (CUI) is an 8-character identifier beginning with the letter "C" and followed by 7 digits.  Each concept is assigned such a CUI.  The CUI has no intrinsic meaning but remains constant through time and across versions._Value Domain for java language String datatype.
